=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Control_ex3 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: stable
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -15.9794
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5007
  pitch_clarity: 483.3284
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -6.0632
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Control Example 3
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Control.html
// Tags: Control, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 3 ---
a = { SinOsc.ar(\freq.kr(440, 1.2)) }.play;
a.set(\freq, 330);
a.release;
a = { SinOsc.ar(\freq.kr([440, 460], 1.2)) }.play;
a.setn(\freq, [330, 367]);
a.release;
